sentences: António Pinho Vargas (born Vila Nova de Gaia, August 15, 1951) is a Portuguese composer and pianist specializing in  jazz and contemporary music.
Having obtained a degree in history at the University of Porto, he studied music at the Rotterdam Conservatory from 1987 to 1990 and graduated with a degree in Musical Composition.
In 1991, he began teaching musical composition at the Escola Superior de Música in Lisbon.
His first jazz album was Outros Lugares (1983).
